    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-25T15:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-25T15:53:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–2454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d602fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SPJ1"
                            >Sturm</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>. Repeated to Paris as telegram 4244 and to
                        Saigon as telegram 2403.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-25T16:53:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1954—4:53 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 121. Reference <gloss target="#t_Dulte1"
                        >Dulte</gloss>s 103<note n="2" xml:id="d602fn2">Dated May 24, <ref
                            target="#pg_900">p. 900</ref>.</note> and 107.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d602fn3">Dated May 24, <ref target="#pg_902">p. 902</ref>.</note>
                    Your talk with <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> effectively clears
                    way for developing direct personal contact between you and <persName
                        corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName>.<note n="4" xml:id="d602fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> reported in telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 115, May 26, that “through intermediary
                        appointed by <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> I have suggested
                        a conversation with <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> but have
                        indicated this might take place after French Assembly debate on Indochina
                        now scheduled for June 1st.” (396.1 GE/5–2654)</note> Reports your further
                    conversations with <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> will assist us
                    in decisions which may have to be taken quickly.</p>
                <p>Despite rapid course of events in Vietnam, we fear that <persName
                        corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BLP1">Buu
                        Loc</persName> government lack sense urgency and believe we should do all
                    possible to encourage them to initiate prompt and radical action.</p>
                <p>As indicated, <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> portion <gloss
                        target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 110<note n="5" xml:id="d602fn5">Dated May
                        22, <ref target="#pg_892">p. 892</ref>.</note> was intended serve only as
                    background and not as subject specific discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
